<body>
    <h2>Intro</h2>
        <p>You have 2 identities that require protection, and you need to pay more attention 
        to your digital identity. It is important because you have your personal information on the
         internet, and if you’re not careful, then you can lose everything and ruin yourself.</p>

    <h2>Brief description</h2>
      <p>Digital personal security is protecting your online identity and information from anyone 
      who you don't want to have access to it</p>

      <h2>Who started this?</h2>

      <p>Ray Tomlinson, he also invented email; he wrote another program called Reaper, the
       first antivirus software which would chase Creeper(a virus at the time) and delete it.</p>





    <h2>Why does it exist/ what do people gain?</h2>
        <p>criminals have a lot to gain from digital information, they could ruin your finances, personal relationships/ reputation in a matter of hours
         with just a few login credentials. Big corporations also have incentive to gather and analyze your data as to sell it to marketing firms. 
</p>

    <h2>Four interesting facts</h2>
        <p>the internet was not designed with privacy in mind, The number of cyber attacks is going UP not down, 
        160,000 Facebook accounts are compromised per day, 147.9 million consumers had data (like SSN’s) stolen in Equifax breach</p>

    <h2>Examples from history</h2>
        <p>The U.S. Justice Department uncovered a major government-backed Iranian cyber-espionage ring. These hackers broke into the computer networks of 144 U.S. universities, stole 31 terabytes of intellectual property. </p>
    
    <h2>How does it affect coding or online culture</h2> 
        <p>It opens jobs for people in the technological world. In 2016, there were only 100,000 jobs opened for Digital Security, and that number has increased by 28% since then. The field has become very predominant in our technological society. It also means that every day people have to be diligent and take extra precautions in order to secure their information </p>
        
